{"key":"post-13779336","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13779336</id>\n<content>If your grains or brf cakes are fully colonized, you can spawn them to bulk.&amp;nbsp; The (minimum) one week consolidation phase is before introducing to fruiting conditions, and many species require much longer than that.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In the early days, too much emphasis was placed on 'speed of colonization' which was flat-out misdirected.&amp;nbsp; That's why growers today get up to triple the harvest of growers of even five or ten years ago.&amp;nbsp; Previously, they didn't understand the concept of allowing the mycelium to digest more of the substrate before fruiting.&amp;nbsp; For some reason, they thought that was a bad thing.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13779813</next>\n<prev>13779332</prev>\n<first>13779244</first>\n<last>13779813</last>\n<when>1294937391</when>\n<utime>01/13/11 06:49 PM</utime>\n</post>"}